ZH: 这是我的亲属，我们是堂姐妹。
EN: This is my relative; we are cousins.

ZH: 我的亲属家族非常庞大。
EN: My extended family is very large.

ZH: 我与你是远亲。
EN: We are distant relatives.

ZH: 他们是我的近亲，我很亲近他们。
EN: They are my close relatives, and I feel close to them.

ZH: 我与我的亲属保持着密切联系。
EN: I maintain close contact with my relatives.

ZH: 我们全家亲属都聚在一起庆祝生日。
EN: Our entire family of relatives gathers together to celebrate birthdays.

ZH: 年会上，公司邀请亲属一起参加。
EN: During the annual company gathering, relatives are invited to join as well.

ZH: 我亲属的家庭都在城市里。
EN: My relatives' families all live in the city.

ZH: 他因为亲属的关系而得到了这份工作。
EN: He got this job because of his family connections.

ZH: 亲属之间应该互相关心和帮助。
EN: Relatives should care for and help each other.

ZH: 我与亲属之间有着共同的血脉。
EN: There is a shared bloodline between me and my relatives.

ZH: 亲属关系在中国文化中非常重要。
EN: Kinship is highly valued in Chinese culture.

ZH: 他的亲属迁移到了另一个国家。
EN: His relatives migrated to another country.

ZH: 我和我的亲属有共同的祖先。
EN: My relatives and I have a common ancestor.

ZH: 她的亲属都住在乡村里。
EN: Her relatives all live in the countryside.

ZH: 父母是我们最亲近的亲属。
EN: Parents are our closest relatives.

ZH: 我的亲属会举办一个家庭聚会。
EN: My relatives will host a family gathering.

ZH: 亲属间的纽带是非常紧密的。
EN: The bonds between relatives are very strong.

ZH: 我希望在假期能与亲属一起度过时间。
EN: I hope to spend time with relatives during the holidays.

ZH: 这是一部关于亲属关系的纪录片。
EN: This is a documentary about kinship.
